Project Summary

Services Delivered

Consultant: Antoine Schuppisser Role: Senior UX/UI & Product Design Consultant Environment: European Commission, DG COMM Period: 2024 - 2025
01

User Research Approach

Methods applied across both projects to ground design decisions in evidence

◎

Stakeholder Interviews

Semi-structured interviews with product owners, editorial teams, studio coordinators and technical leads to capture business goals, pain points and operational constraints.

DiscoveryAlignment
◉

Usage Scenario Mapping

Identification and documentation of key usage scenarios: live event coverage, media search and download, content scheduling, multi-channel publication. Each scenario mapped end-to-end with user goals, touchpoints and friction points.

DiscoveryModelling
◇

User Persona Definition

Research-backed personas for journalists, media professionals, institutional communicators and production coordinators, based on interview synthesis and behavioural patterns observed across existing platforms.

ResearchStrategy
◆

Heuristic & Comparative Analysis

Systematic evaluation of the existing platforms against Nielsen heuristics and comparable institutional media portals (EP, UN, NATO) to identify usability gaps and benchmark best practices.

EvaluationBenchmark
◎

Task Analysis

Decomposition of critical user tasks into discrete steps, identifying cognitive load, decision points, and areas where the interface could reduce friction or automate repetitive actions.

ResearchInteraction
◉

Validation Workshops

Iterative design review sessions with cross-functional stakeholders. Prototype walkthroughs, scenario-based feedback, and priority alignment using structured critique frameworks.

ValidationCo-design

Research Artefacts Produced

User persona sheets with goals, frustrations, and behavioural patterns
Scenario maps documenting end-to-end user journeys per audience segment
Heuristic evaluation reports with severity ratings and recommendations
Stakeholder interview synthesis with prioritized insights
Task flow diagrams highlighting friction points and design opportunities
Workshop session reports with decisions log and action items
02

AV Portal

Audiovisual Platform, public-facing website redesign

Public Website Redesign

Led the end-to-end UX/UI redesign of the European Commission's audiovisual portal, serving journalists, media professionals, and institutional users. The redesign focused on improving content discoverability, live event access, and editorial workflows while aligning the interface with the eUI Design System (v21).

Interface Screenshots
Homepage: hero banner, live streaming section, top stories & latest content
Video detail: player, metadata & related media
Photo report: media detail & gallery view
1

Discovery & User Needs Analysis

Stakeholder interviews and usage scenario mapping across three primary audiences: press/journalists seeking event coverage, media professionals downloading assets, and institutional users managing content. Identified critical gaps in search, filtering and live event navigation.

2

Information Architecture Restructuring

Redesigned the navigation model and content hierarchy based on task analysis findings. Introduced faceted search patterns, contextual entry points for live events, and streamlined pathways from discovery to download.

3

Prototyping & Iterative Validation

High-fidelity prototypes in Figma, tested through structured walkthrough sessions with editorial teams and technical stakeholders. Multiple design iterations informed by scenario-based feedback and accessibility audits.

4

Implementation Handoff

Comprehensive specifications for the development team: component documentation, interaction states, responsive behaviour, and accessibility requirements aligned with WCAG 2.1 AA standards.

03

Mermaid

Content Production Planner, internal tool

Planning & Coordination Tool

Designed a planning and coordination tool supporting audiovisual content production across recording studios, editorial teams, and publication channels. The tool formalises previously manual scheduling and tracking processes into a structured, collaborative interface.

Interface Screenshot
Weekly planner view: staff scheduling, event cards & production coordination
1

Process Discovery & Workflow Modelling

Workshops with studio coordinators, editors, and production managers to map existing processes. Documented task lifecycles, handoff points, dependencies, and bottlenecks across the content production chain.

2

Operational Dashboard & Scheduling Logic

Defined the dashboard structure and scheduling model based on task analysis: resource allocation, timeline views, status tracking, and cross-team visibility. Designed for both daily operational use and weekly planning reviews.

3

Interaction Design & Specifications

Wireframes and UI specifications covering task creation, assignment, status transitions, calendar views, and publication workflows. Handoff documentation structured for Angular development within the EU Component Library framework.

4

Stakeholder Communication & Alignment

Continuous facilitation between business owners, operational teams, and developers. Translated complex production requirements into clear design decisions, ensuring alignment across all parties throughout the design process.

Antoine Schuppisser - Senior UX/UI Consultant - European Commission, DG COMM
